</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
UNREAD MAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
How many times are we told to "write your congressman -- they care about what 
you say"? 
</P>
<P>
Even though we scoff, I do write. 
</P>
<P>
For the second time, I received a letter back from state Rep. Dana Rohrabacher 
(R-Lomita), thanking me for my letter, BUT, once again, he thanks me for a 
letter about something I didn't write. A case in point: I wrote him to stop 
sending military aid to El Salvador. His letter explained about how he voted 
"no" on his new salary raise. 
</P>
<P>
I say, "Don't answer your mail if you don't read it." 
</P>
<P>
EILEEN MURPHY 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
