<HEADLINE>
<P>
KOVIC STATEMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am writing in response to Ron Kovic's statement (Jan. 9) that he is " . . . 
asking people to write to me, to call me, to come up to me on the street. . . . 
" 
</P>
<P>
I have not forgotten Vietnam or the connection of Vietnam to what is happening 
with the United States today, both in domestic and international arenas. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Dornan is an epitome of the worst of this country. I thought your 
characterization of him as appealing to people's fears was exactly right. I 
also think it showed considerable political acumen about how you might pitch a 
campaign to defeat him. 
</P>
<P>
NANCY PRESS 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
