<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: DEL MAR'S SEYMOUR IN SEMIFINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Top-seeded Bob Seymour of Del Mar moved into the semifinals of the men's 65s 
singles in the San Diego Super Seniors tennis tournament Wednesday with an 
impressive, 6-0, 6-0 victory over Larry Tarbell of Brea at the San Diego Tennis 
&amp; Racquet Club. 
</P>
<P>
Seymour will face third-seeded Clare Hoke of Claremont, who defeated Tom 
Brotherton of Fallbrook, 6-3, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
Second-seeded Stan Potts of San Diego defeated Don Fiebing, 6-3, 6-3. Potts 
will play Art Graybill of Rolling Hills, who defeated Al Olson of San Diego, 
6-1, 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
FOOTBALL 
</P>
<P>
Defensive end Lee Williams and defensive back Gill Byrd of the Chargers were 
named to The Sporting News All-Pro team. San Francisco quarterback Joe Montana 
was picked as the Player of the Year. 
</P>
<P>
BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
Third baseman Romy Cucjen, a 1980 graduate of Bonita Vista, was traded 
Wednesday from the St. Louis Cardinals to the Indianapolis Indians, an American 
Assn. (triple-A) affiliate of the Montreal Expos, for pitcher Isaac Alleyne. 
Cucjen, 27, batted .276 with the Louisville Redbirds last year. He was acquired 
by the St. Louis organization from San Francisco. 
</P>
