<P>
Palomar League 
</P>
<P>
Mt. Carmel 60, Poway 53 -- No. 1 Mt. Carmel (10-3, 3-0) led after the first 
quarter, 22-4, and host Poway spent the rest of the game playing catch-up. The 
No. 4 Titans (10-2, 1-2) cut the Mt. Carmel lead to 10 at the half, 34-24, but 
couldn't finish the comeback. 
</P>
<P>
"Mt. Carmel did a good job early," Poway Coach Neville Saner said. "They ran 
the break well, and we didn't defend well. They got right after us." 
</P>
<P>
Mt. Carmel surprised Poway by starting its big lineup -- Shane Knight 
(6-feet-9), Ryan Wootton (6-4), Mike Graves (6-3), Jeff Blake (6-6) and Bill 
Wootton (6-3). Bill Wootton led Mt. Carmel with 17 points. Dana Pope had 14, 
and Knight had 11. Matt Fletcher led Poway with 16 points, including four 
three-pointers. 
