Eagles to the Super Bowl but members of one church think he's super. He stunned 
them by showing up at Sunday services with a $100,000 donation for the 
500-member church. "They were rejoicing," said Elva Smith, of St. John Baptist 
Church in east Camden, N.J. Cunningham isn't a member of the church but has 
attended often. The church will use the money for construction and a local 
outreach program. 
</P>
<P>
Smoke-Out: Social activist Dick Gregory, jailed Monday for intentionally 
trespassing in the Smoke Connection, a Milwaukee shop that sells drug 
paraphernalia, paid bail and was released Tuesday. YEMI TOURE 
