<HEADLINE>
<P>
COOK IT LIGHT: PLUCKING FAT FROM HERB CHICKEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNE JONES, Jones is a food consultant and a cookbook author. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DEAR JEANNE: I have a favorite recipe from a local restaurant, but as you can 
see it is loaded with calories and fat. My husband and I are on low-fat, 
low-calorie and low-cholesterol diets, so could you convert this recipe for us? 
</P>
<P>
 -- LOIS, Marysville, Wash. 
</P>
<P>
CHEESE-AND-HERB-STUFFED CHICKEN 
</P>
<P>
2 eggs, lightly beaten 
</P>
<P>
4 ounces cubed chicken 
</P>
<P>
2 (3-ounce) packages cream cheese, softened 
</P>
<P>
4 ounces grated Parmesan cheese 
</P>
<P>
3 ounces chevre cheese 
</P>
<P>
1/4 cup whipping cream 
</P>
<P>
2 green onions, chopped 
</P>
<P>
1 teaspoon dried oregano 
</P>
<P>
1 ounce sun-dried tomatoes, finely chopped 
</P>
<P>
2 ounces fresh chopped spinach 
</P>
<P>
10 boneless chicken breast halves 
</P>
<P>
Oil or butter 
</P>
<P>
Combine eggs, chicken, cream, Parmesan and chevre cheeses and whipping cream in 
food processor. Process until smooth, remove and place in bowl. 
</P>
<P>
Mix in green onions, oregano, tomatoes and spinach by hand, blending 
thoroughly. Set aside. 
</P>
<P>
Cut pocket in each chicken breast by placing on flat surface and inserting 
sharp knife in large end of breast. Cut to within 1/2 inch of sides and end to 
form pocket. Do not cut entirely through small end of breast. 
</P>
<P>
Using pastry bag fitted with 1/2-inch round tip, pipe cheese mixture into 
pockets. Arrange stuffed chicken breasts in baking pan, brush with oil or 
butter and bake at 375 degrees 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 10 servings. 
</P>
<P>
DEAR LOIS: Part-skim ricotta cheese works well in place of the cream cheese, 
and I was able to replace the whipping cream with nonfat milk without an 
appreciable difference in the finished product. I also found I could eliminate 
the egg yolks. 
</P>
<P>
 -- JEANNE 
</P>
<P>
LIGHTER CHEESE-AND-HERB-STUFFED CHICKEN 
</P>
<P>
3 egg whites, lightly beaten 
</P>
<P>
4 ounces uncooked chicken breast, cubed 
</P>
<P>
3 ounces part-skim ricotta cheese 
</P>
<P>
4 ounces Parmesan cheese, grated 
</P>
<P>
3 ounces chevre cheese 
</P>
<P>
1/4 cup nonfat milk 
</P>
<P>
2 green onions, chopped 
</P>
<P>
1 teaspoon dried oregano 
</P>
<P>
1 ounce sun-dried tomatoes, finely chopped 
</P>
<P>
2 ounces fresh spinach, chopped 
</P>
<P>
10 boneless, skinned chicken breast halves 
</P>
<P>
Combine egg whites, cubed chicken, ricotta, Parmesan and chevre cheeses and 
milk in food processor. Process until smooth, remove and place in bowl. Mix in 
green onions, oregano, tomatoes and spinach by hand, blending thoroughly. Set 
aside. 
</P>
<P>
Cut pocket in each chicken breast by placing on flat surface and inserting 
sharp knife in large end of breast. Cut to within 1/2 inch of sides and end to 
form pocket. Do not cut entirely through small end of breast. 
</P>
<P>
Fill each pocket with 1/3 cup cheese mixture. Arrange stuffed chicken breasts 
in baking pan and bake at 375 degrees 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 10 servings. 
</P>
<P>
Each serving contains approximately: 
</P>
<P>
Original Recipe: 
</P>
<P>
415 calories 
</P>
<P>
172 mg cholesterol 
</P>
<P>
27 gm fat 
</P>
<P>
443 mg sodium 
</P>
<P>
Revised Recipe: 
</P>
<P>
259 calories 
</P>
<P>
97 mg cholesterol 
</P>
<P>
8 gm fat 
</P>
<P>
413 mg sodium 
</P>
</TEXT>
