<P>
GOLF FEES WILL INCREASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Teeing off at the Alhambra Golf Course is going to be a little more expensive 
beginning Feb. 1. 
</P>
<P>
To help pay for general maintenance and improvements at the 18-hole course, the 
City Council on Monday voted to raise fees by amounts ranging from 50 cents to 
$2, depending on when the rounds are played. Under the new formula, for 
example, playing 18 holes on a weekend would cost $14, up from $12. 
</P>
<P>
The proposed increases have been posted at the city golf course since early 
December, and there have been no complaints from players, said Jerry Wisz, a 
golf professional who manages the course. 
</P>
