<P>
AUDIT OF HOSPITAL SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To help solve Alhambra Community Hospital's money problems and at the same time 
end the city's financial woes, the City Council has introduced an ordinance 
calling for an audit of hospital operations. 
</P>
<P>
Final approval of the audit requires a second council vote. 
</P>
<P>
In a separate action Monday, the council also voted to place on the April 
ballot a measure asking voters to repeal a 1982 initiative that set conditions 
on the sale of the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
The hospital, owned by the Alhambra Redevelopment Agency, has fallen behind in 
its rent payments, forcing the council to cut the city budget and increase 
municipal fees. 
</P>
