SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: GLENDORA; 
</P>
<P>
NEW BONDS FOR OLD DEBT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council voted Tuesday to issue about $25 million in new bonds to take 
advantage of current lower interest rates in paying off the Glendora Community 
Redevelopment Agency debt. 
</P>
<P>
The agency owes $10.4 million from three bond issues with interest rates of 
more than 9%. The new bonds, which will be retired in 20 years, will be at 
7.7%. The new bonds will also generate $5.3 million for capital projects, $3.2 
million to repay loans from the city, and $4.5 million toward buying property 
for low- and moderate-income housing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
