<HEADLINE>
<P>
4.2 QUAKE RATTLES TEHACHAPIS NORTH OF MOJAVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A magnitude 4.2 earthquake hit the Tehachapi Mountains, 12 miles north of 
Mojave in Kern County, on Wednesday, but authorities said they had received no 
reports of damage or injuries. 
</P>
<P>
Although the quake was centered near the California Aqueduct, workers on the 
waterway said they did not feel the temblor. 
</P>
<P>
Seismologists at Caltech in Pasadena said several small earthquakes had 
occurred in the area over the last several weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
