<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHO'S HOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Loyola Marymount's Bo Kimble was named Windex College Player of the Week after 
scoring 38, 54 and 32 points in road games, including a 35-footer at the buzzer 
to beat St. Joseph's of Philadelphia, 99-96. He leads the nation in scoring at 
37.4 and is averaging 44.6 points and 9.5 rebounds in his last seven games. 
</P>
<P>
Mira Costa guard Chris Hobbs scored 20 of his game-high 30 points in the second 
half Tuesday to help the Mustangs erase a 26-24 halftime deficit and defeat 
Centennial, 60-46. It was Mira Costa's seventh straight win and kept the team 
tied for first in the Ocean League at 3-0. 
</P>
<P>
Hawthorne's press claimed another victim Tuesday as the Cougars forced 22 
turnovers against Santa Monica and won, 73-54, to remain in a first-place tie 
in the Bay League at 3-0. 
</P>
<P>
Lisa Leslie and Janet Davis combined for 34 points and 23 rebounds to lead 
Morningside's girls basketball team to its 75th straight Ocean League victory 
Tuesday over West Torrance, 91-49. 
</P>
<P>
Who's Not 
</P>
<P>
Rolling Hills' basketball team, three-time defending Bay League champion, fell 
to Inglewood, 68-65, Tuesday to open league play with an 0-3 record. It marks 
the first time in five seasons under Coach Cliff Warren that the Titans have 
lost three consecutive games. 
</P>
<P>
The Cal State Dominguez Hills basketball team made just six of 24 field-goal 
attempts in the first half of Saturday's 58-44 loss to Biola. The Toros (4-9) 
take a two-game losing streak into Friday's game at Cal Poly Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
West Torrance's basketball team was outscored, 42-13, in the first half Tuesday 
en route to a 92-45 Ocean League loss to Morningside. The Warriors dropped to 
2-9 overall and 0-3 in league play. 
</P>
<P>
North Torrance's hopes for a turnaround this season appear in jeopardy after 
the Saxons suffered their fifth consecutive loss, 67-54, to Redondo, falling to 
0-3 in the Ocean League and 5-9 overall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
