<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANIEL CERONE, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gumbel Back on Golf Tour: "Today" host Bryant Gumbel, who began his 
broadcasting career as a sportscaster for KNBC in Los Angeles, will dust off 
his spikes and return to sports as the host of NBC Sports' 1990 professional 
golf coverage. Gumbel, who will continue his "Today" role, will begin his 
duties on the putting green at the Bob Hope Classic, Jan. 20-21. . . . And teen 
pop idols New Kids on the Block will star in a half-hour, live-action/animated 
Saturday-morning series debuting in the fall on ABC. DANIEL CERONE 
</P>
