<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Twenty-one U.S. track and field athletes, including Edwin Moses and Jackie 
Joyner-Kersee, tested negative for drugs in the latest batch of random tests, 
The Athletics Congress said. 
</P>
<P>
The TAC report covered four separate testing periods starting the week of Nov. 
20. The year-round testing program began Oct. 2. No athletes have tested 
positive, although several who failed to show up for the tests are under 
investigation. 
</P>
