<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
All-American linebacker Keith McCants said the Alabama coaching change would 
not affect his decision on whether to skip his senior season and enter the NFL 
draft. 
</P>
<P>
Despite reports that the 6-foot-5, 256-pound McCants will turn professional, 
possibly becoming the No. 1 choice in the draft, he would not say if he will 
give up his final year of collegiate eligibility. 
</P>
<P>
"I have not announced that I am coming out for the draft," he said. "I'm still 
a junior and I'm registered at the University of Alabama for the second 
semester. 
</P>
<P>
McCants said his eventual announcement would have "nothing to do with Coach 
Curry." 
</P>
