<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Murad Muhammad filed a lawsuit against fellow boxing promoter Don King, asking 
in excess of $8 million. 
</P>
<P>
The suit stems from heavyweight champion Mike Tyson's proposed fight against 
Canadian Razor Ruddock last November in Edmonton, Canada. Tyson pulled out 
because of illness. Muhammad handles Ruddock's fights. 
</P>
<P>
Tyson, who now is scheduled to fight Buster Douglas on Feb. 12 in Tokyo, is not 
named in the suit. Douglas' fights also are promoted by King. 
</P>
<P>
The suit seeks not only damages, but an injunction against King promoting Tyson 
fights until Ruddock has a title shot. The injunction would begin after the 
Tyson-Douglas fight. 
</P>
</TEXT>
