<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MALATHION SPRAYING CANCELED BECAUSE OF FOG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Citing dense fog that moved in over the Southland, county agricultural 
officials canceled Wednesday night's spraying of the pesticide Malathion in the 
battle against the Medfly. 
</P>
<P>
Helicopters were expected to cover a 53-square-mile area over Rosemead and 
Monrovia and parts of Pasadena, San Marino, Arcadia, Temple City, Alhambra, San 
Gabriel, Monterey Park, Montebello, South El Monte and El Monte. 
</P>
<P>
An agriculture department representative said the spraying will be rescheduled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
