<HEADLINE>
<P>
5TH TUNNEL WORKER KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DOVER, England 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A worker helping build the Channel Tunnel between Britain and France was struck 
by an underground train and killed Wednesday, the fifth person to die on the 
project, Kent County police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
