<TEXT>
<P>
China today dismissed as "utterly illegal and absurd" an approach by Taiwan to 
join the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade. 
</P>
<P>
A Foreign Ministry spokesman said the Geneva-based world trade watchdog 
organization must reject the application. 
</P>
<P>
Taiwan's Economic Ministry said a week ago that the island had formally applied 
to join GATT as an independent customs territory. 
</P>
<P>
By filing the application, the spokesman told a briefing for foreign 
journalists here, the Taiwan authorities were posing as the government of a 
sovereign country although the island is part of the only legal Chinese state, 
ruled by Beijing. Both Beijing and Taipei insist that there can be only one 
true China. 
